Whatâ€™s the different between the EASY and HARD levels?
The EASY level has on-screen hits that indicate what the face parts
should look like; the HARD level does not have these hints.
Does my child need to know how to read to use this app?
A basic level of reading is necessary to read the emotion requested. If
your child does not read yet, we recommend using the app alongside
him or her, for guidance on this.
Can I print the face comparison page, after the selfie is taken?
You sure can! When you reach the comparison page, simultaneously
press the Sleep/Awake button (located at the top of the iPas) and the
Home button. This takes a screenshot, which will automatically be saved
to your photos. To print, go to the Photos app and find the screenshot.
Tap on the share button (in the lower right-hand corner) and find the
option to print. You can also share this photo via email, text message, or
through a variety of other apps.
